Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
delete_cell_obs(25.10)                                  delete_cell_obs(25.10)

Name
       delete_cell_obs

Syntax
       delete_cell_obs

       [-help]

        -cells {base_cell | design | module}+

       {-obs_shapes  <shape>+  | [{-rects {{<llx1 lly1 urx1 ury1>} {<llx2 lly2
       urx2 ury2>}...} | -polygon {<x1 y1 x2 y2 x3 y3> ...}] -layers <layer>+}

       Helps in deleting an obstruction geometry or library obstruction for  a
       cell on the specified layer. This command deletes the obstruction geom-
       etry  added by the add_cell_obs command or library obstruction (SPACING
       0 OBS).

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each delete_cell_obs parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man delete_cell_obs

       -cells {base_cell | design | module}+
              Specifies the cell name or pointer.

       -layers <layer>+
              Specifies the layer name or pointer.

       -obs_shapes <shape>+
              Specifies the cell obstruction shape pointers.

              Note: This parameter must be used with the -cells parameter, and
              cannot be specified with any other parameter except than -help.

       -polygon {<x1 y1 x2 y2 x3 y3> < ...>}
              Specifies the polygon shape.

       -rects {{<llx1 lly1 urx1 ury1>} {<llx2 lly2 urx2 ury2>}...}
              Specifies the Obs rect list for deleting obstruction geometries.

Examples
       Following is an example of using the -obs_shapes parameter for specify-
       ing the cell obstruction shape pointer:

              * The BUFX1 cell has multiple obs shapes on different layers:

                dbget   [dbget   top.insts.cell.name   BUFX1   -p].allObstruc-
                tions.shapes

                 0x7fd9ee9941e0  0x7fd9ee9941c0  0x7fd9ee9941a0 0x7fd9ee994180
                0x7fd9ee994160

              * The following command deletes the  first  two  shapes  in  the
                list:

                delete_cell_obs  -obs_shapes  {0x7fd9ee9941e0  0x7fd9ee9941c0}
                -cells BUFX1

Related Information
       add_cell_obs

